betterquesting:10.desc:8: On your island, there is a Barrel that contains all the basic Seeds, as well as a Watering Can.
As it is in almost every Minecraft mod pack, the first thing you are going to need to do is punching a tree, the Lime tree on your island, to be specific.

Before you can even start farming, you are going to need to plant your Crops. You can't simply plant them on Grass. You are going to need to first till the ground with a Wooden Hoe, place Crop Sticks on it and then plant the Seeds.

 There is more that you can do with Crop Sticks though. Placing empty Crop Sticks adjacent to a fully grown crop to have it spread. By putting 2 Crop Sticks on top of each other between different types of Crops, they will cross-breed.
While tilling Grass, you managed to obtain a Worm. Worms will till the ground in a 3x3 area around them tilled and hydrated.

As you can see, you only have a finite amount of Water for the time being. With that said, you should cross-breed Fire and Ice Seeds to obtain Water Seeds. You can use the Water Essence from this crop to add a Bucket worth of Water to the Barrel.
By cross-breeding Wheat and Water Crops, you can obtain Dirt Crops.
By cross-breeding Water and Fire Crops, you can obtain Stone Crops.
On Sand, you can cross-breed Beetroots and Wheat, to obtain Sugar Canes.
With Fire and Dirt Essence, you can make Sand.

To find out the stats of your Seeds, you can use a Seed Analyzer. Once you know the stats of your Seeds, you can breed them together with other Crops of the same type to create Crops with better stats.
As you have probably noticed, you only have 2 hearts to start with. By eating different foods, you can gain more.

You can cross-breed Melons and Dirt Crops to obtain Nature Crops. With Nature Essence, you can make most vanilla plants, so you won't have to have them as separate plants. Combining them with other types of Essence, you can make the different types of soil and Saplings.
One of the things you can make with Nature Essence is Mycelium. By cross-breeding Potatoes and Carrots on Mycelium, you can obtain Mushrooms.
By cross-breeding Dirt and Nature Crops, you can obtain Wood Crops.
Mobs simply don't spawn, so you can't make a mob spawner. Luckly, you can now cross-breed Mushrooms and Nature Crops to obtain Zombie Crops.
Mobs don't spawn naturally, but that doesn't mean they can't be hatched from Eggs. You can cross-breed Nature and Stone Crops to obtain Chicken Crops.

For automatic farming, you can use a Farmer.
Instead of using a Watering can the entire time, you can have Sprinklers. They need to have Water piped into the bottom in order to work.
In order to have infinite water, you are going to need a Endervoir.
The market will allow you to buy all Pam's HarvestCraft Seeds with Emeralds. Additionally, it allows you to buy Saplings and Spawn Eggs.
For advanced automation, you are going to need an ME or RS system. It all starts with the Controller.

Prosperity Shards are needed for making all the gear from Mystical Agriculture. To obtain them, you are going to have to attune yourself with Aevitas, which will give you a perk that spawns the Ore in Stone around you, or Minerllis, which will give you a perk that adds a chance for it to be dropped when mining Stone.
The simplest form of flight in this pack is using a Jetpack. However, there are several types to choose from.
While you can't use a smeltery for making common alloys, you can still use it for making powerful tools, but most importantly; Gears! Gears are one of the most basic components of machines.
Using mob Essences and Spawner Shards, you are able to create the corresponding Broken Mob Spanwers and combne them with a Powered Spawner in an Anvil to spawn the corresponding mobs.
This is your goal in this pack: the Creative Vending Upgrade.
You can set up a simple Irrigation System with a Tank, Channel and Sprinkler to automatically water your Crops. The Tank can collect rain Water or have Water piped into it.
You can put an AgriCultural Journal in the Analyzer to get extra information about the Crop you're analyzing, such as required light level and growth stages.

The Quantum Chest allows you to store the 32 bit integer-worth of one type of item. Would be quite handy for those Essences.
Ember is required to get started with the Embers mod. To make an Ember Crystal, put a Plorb with Blazing Pyrotheum in a Vacuum Freezer. Simple, right?
To start off with ThaumCraft, you are going to need to make the basic Vis Crystals, throw one on the ground and pick it up. Then, the mod will guide you through itself.
By cross-breeding Coal and Graphite Crops, you can obtain HOP Graphite Crops.
A Cooking Table allows you to automatically craft foods as long as you have all the ingredients and tools in the corresponding parts of the multiblock.

The Master Infusion Crystal has infinite durability, making it most suitable for autocrafting essence, it can transmute all Essences and even in Block form. To make it however, you are going to need all the previous tiers of Infusion Crystals.
By squeezing Lead Crystals, you can obtain Chaos Fragments.

To make some things in Embers, you are going to need Archaic Bricks. They can be made through a similar way Terrasteel is normally made. You still have the Terrestrial Agglomerration Plate, but under it and on the edges you have Scorched Grass and on the corners you have Firewood. Then you just throw in Coke Dust and a Caminite Brick on the Plate and as Terrasteel, the recipe uses half a Mana Pool.
By cross-breeding Cucumbers and Melons, you can obtain Giga Pickles.
